                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north base of the central shrine in the Maṅgaḷapurīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Jaṭāvarmaṉ Vikramapāṇḍya. Year 3: 1403 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The details of date given, viz., <hi rend="bold">Vṛiśchika, śu 5, Sunday, Tiruvōṇam</hi>, correspond to</p>						
                            
                            <p>1403 A.D., November 18, Sunday.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This record registers a grant of land as <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi</hi> along with specified taxes to god Tiruchchōpuram-uḍaiya nāyaṉār at Tyāgavalli in Mēṟkāl-nāḍu, a subdivision of Virudarājabhayaṅkara-vaḷanāḍu towards the expenses of providing worship, offerings and unguents in the temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Among the boundaries of the land is mentioned <hi rend="italic">Avaṉivichchādiraṉ</hi> (vidyādharaṉ) <hi rend="italic">tōppu.</hi></p>						
                            
                        </summary>
